-- test-d/stanza.cabal.draft — the cabal edit D's freeze commit
-- applies to proplang.cabal (drafted in the oracle phase per the
-- manifest-covers-build-files convention: cabal edits land only at
-- freeze boundaries, reviewed with the pack).
--
-- ONE stanza this increment (HOSTS_D_PACK sections 10/11): the
-- test-d oracle suite. Gate 5 (`cabal test all`) absorbs it — the
-- TENTH suite — with no edit to any frozen audit script. No new
-- executable: the wire rows drive H's proplang-govhost (whose
-- latent@1 path lands with D's implementation), reached through the
-- SAME build-tool-depends; the oracle-phase red-run supplies
-- GOVHOST_EXE instead.
--
-- The increment's OTHER freeze-commit edits are enumerated in the
-- pack (HOSTS_D_PACK section 11, all author-applied): the CLAUDE.md
-- porting-order amendment (D before A; D0 subsumed — author text,
-- R3), the HOSTS_PLAN.md amendments (8.12 resolved, section 9
-- reordered, section 6's observation space outcome-first), the
-- membrane-wire.md v2 latent@1 section (or its successor doc), and
-- the manifest extension + re-sign over test-d/ and the amended
-- texts. host-governor/WireU.hs stays OUT of the manifest like
-- Wire.hs (implementation surface, ruling H-7). Census target:
-- EMPTY — witnessed by gCensus and the nine prior suites staying
-- green (no frozen assertion literal moves; the src additions are
-- new sorts, faces and grids behind DROP_UPILOT/DROP_UWALK).

test-suite test-d
  import:           warnings
  type:             exitcode-stdio-1.0
  main-is:          D.hs
  other-modules:    Wire
                  , WireU
  hs-source-dirs:   test-d, host-governor
  build-depends:    base
                  , proplang
                  , tasty
                  , tasty-hunit
                  , process
  build-tool-depends: proplang:proplang-govhost
  default-language: GHC2021
